{"body": "[Do not merge]\r\n\r\nfirst pass of adding parallelization\r\n\r\n* adding hooks for before.batch and after.batch   (think I should rename to before.fork and after.hook)\r\n* added a new runner -- ParallelRunner, which loops over all of the scenarios (not the features) batches them up for n workers to have at them, then joins the threads and regroups the scenarios into featureResults\r\n* adds option --parallel / -p which you can pass -n- for the number of processes you want to have processing your tests\r\n\r\nbut with these hooks the implementer can set up there forked process.  I also set a world.port_number for the implementer to use that to setup webservers and other resources specifically to each fork.\r\n\r\nStill very much in beta -- and I have some ideas to make it faster -- but seems promising\r\n\r\nKnown issues:\r\n* need docs\r\n* need tests\r\n\r\nLove Feedback -- is this something that you would consider pulling in.  If so I can work on the known issues, and other feedback that you might have.\r\n\r\nHappy Holidays!", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/gabrielfalcao/lettuce/issues/416/events", "updated_at": "2013-12-21T19:48:44Z", "labels_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/gabrielfalcao/lettuce/issues/416/labels{/name}", "labels": [], "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/gabrielfalcao/lettuce/issues/416/comments", "html_url": "https://github.com/gabrielfalcao/lettuce/pull/416", "number": 416, "assignee": null, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jtushman/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jtushman/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jtushman/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/jtushman", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jtushman/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/jtushman", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jtushman/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://gravatar.com/avatar/3a461d8980e17