{"body": "When I use relative import in ``XXX-steps.py`` located in ``features`` directory, the ValueError occur at line 42 of https://github.com/gabrielfalcao/lettuce/blob/master/lettuce/fs.py\r\n\r\nThe way to fix it is a little bit complicated. Adding ``features`` directory path to ``sys.path`` and import with ``__import__('zzz')``  (current strategy you take) doesn't allow me to use relative import. What all you need to do is that you have to add project root directory path to ``sys.path `` and use ``__import__('xxx.yyy.features.zzz')`` to make it work. \r\n\r\nRelative import is really useful when I create standalone (re-usable) application of Django. Otherwise I have to rewrite the tests again every time when I want to use previously created standalone application in different Django project :-(\r\n\r\nThis is a critical issue for me and I think is for everyone who create re-usable application not only for Django, so could you fix this issue? If I could fix it with myself but the issue is in main strategy of lettuce so it is too complicated for me to handle it.\r\n\r\nThanks for reading.", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/gabrielfalcao/lettuce/issues/203/events", "updated_at": "2011-12-20T21:04:59Z", "labels_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/gabrielfalcao/lettuce/issues/203/labels{/name}", "labels": [{"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/gabrielfalcao/lettuce/labels/brainstorm", "color": "454545", "name": "brainstorm"}, {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/gabrielfalcao/lettuce/labels/in+analysis", "color": "002bff", "name": "in analysis"}], "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/gabrielfalcao/lettuce/issues/203/comments", "html_url": "https://github.com/gabrielfalcao/lettuce/issues/203", "number": 203, "assignee": null, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/lambdalisue/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/lambdalisue/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/lam