{"body": "I've made a very simple 2-step scenario outline (go to an ur> & see if header matches), and provided an extensive amount of examples (over 800). I noticed that lettuce is dying around 270-280 example, due lack of memory - at the moment when it dies it already has almost 2GB of ram - so over 7MB for each example.\r\n\r\nI did some experiments and I noticed a simple relation - the more examples you have, the more memory it takes for each example. After doing some investigation it looks that the problem is with deepcopy in core.Step.solve_and_clone - with each example it is cloning the whole Step object, including things like the scenario (and whatever those things are referring to).\r\n\r\nI guess the solution is to copy explicitly everything that is necessary, I just don't know what all those necessary things are, so I have problem fixing it by myself :)", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/gabrielfalcao/lettuce/issues/194/events", "updated_at": "2013-07-22T05:47:15Z", "labels_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/gabrielfalcao/lettuce/issues/194/labels{/name}", "labels": [], "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/gabrielfalcao/lettuce/issues/194/comments", "html_url": "https://github.com/gabrielfalcao/lettuce/issues/194", "number": 194, "assignee": null, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/pkrzyzaniak/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/pkrzyzaniak/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/pkrzyzaniak/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/pkrzyzaniak", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/pkrzyzaniak/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/pkrzyzaniak", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/pkrzyzaniak/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://gravatar.com/avatar/8654b02db9009b79cbb29a6890ec264b?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F1da917610bd8a3cbe8360bbb8c332a0e.png&r=x", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/pkrzyzaniak/