{"body": "In `lettuce/django/server.py`'s `ThreadedServer`, `run()` creates a pid file in `/tmp/lettuce-django.pid` but never deletes in when it's done. \n\nFurthermore, before it runs, it reads the pid from the pidfile and `kill -9`'s it without any other checks. In a normal scenario, that's probably fine, but it seems like fundamentally dangerous behavior to me.  First, pids wrap around (at 32768 on many systems), so there's a chance it might just go nuclear on some completely random, unrelated process. Second, it seems like a potential security issue. If another user can write a file with the right filename to /tmp, they can cause me to kill a process of their choosing the next time I run lettuce.\n\nThere must be a better way to prevent two instances of the django server from running at the same time.", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/gabrielfalcao/lettuce/issues/259/events", "updated_at": "2012-06-12T20:23:17Z", "labels_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/gabrielfalcao/lettuce/issues/259/labels{/name}", "labels": [], "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/gabrielfalcao/lettuce/issues/259/comments", "html_url": "https://github.com/gabrielfalcao/lettuce/issues/259", "number": 259, "assignee": null, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/thraxil/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/thraxil/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/thraxil/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/thraxil", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/thraxil/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/thraxil", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/thraxil/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://gravatar.com/avatar/a40a8c82858563d739317ec77a5c36ce?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F2d5d4cf93ccf992b3fe617b32b8296a3.png&r=x", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/thraxil/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/thraxil/received_events", "gra