{"body": "As of today lettuce does not use the built in unittest constructs to run it's tests.\r\nThis creates numerous problems:\r\n1. Integration with django requires a special command (See #212).\r\n2. Integration with nose is not possible.\r\n3. Teamcity provdies a way to report test results either throguh the unittest framework or throguh xunit xml output. The xml output feature isn't a very mature and it sometimes does not  generate the xml file correctly (See #200 for an example).\r\n4. I am assuming other CI agents have the same issues. Correct me if I am wrong.\r\n5. The general flexability of lettuce is severely damanged as it is much easier to extend a familiar interface that has more extensibility points.\r\n\r\nI'm opening this issue to discuss how to refactor lettuce to use the unittest framework instead of it's own custom-made test runner.\r\n\r\n@gabrielfalcao Where should we start looking at?", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/gabrielfalcao/lettuce/issues/231/events", "updated_at": "2012-02-28T23:04:45Z", "labels_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/gabrielfalcao/lettuce/issues/231/labels{/name}", "labels": [], "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/gabrielfalcao/lettuce/issues/231/comments", "html_url": "https://github.com/gabrielfalcao/lettuce/issues/231", "number": 231, "assignee": null, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/thedrow/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/thedrow/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/thedrow/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/thedrow", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/thedrow/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/thedrow", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/thedrow/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://gravatar.com/avatar/5bf5f3464f90521d91dc889b71d2955a?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F6c1b3d4b67b87271c3dec4ab370b0a14.png&r=x", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com