{"body": "We currently use TestRail to track our QA testing and we'd like to integrate the output of lettuce with it.  We think it's most effective for lettuce to be the official repository for those tests that we just can't quite automate.  Currently, they're in a spreadsheet.\r\n\r\nUnfortunately, it doesn't make sense to mark them passed or failed.  It would be nice to have a skipped (or better yet, \"run manually\") state.  The idea is that when we do our integration with TestRail, we can ensure that the test is created but hasn't been marked as attempted.  This makes it dead easy for our QA folks to do the remaining tests (without having to separate them into two systems or sort out the ones that need to be done manually).\r\n\r\nIf this isn't something you have the time for, we are also willing to work on the implementation, if you'll accept it.", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/gabrielfalcao/lettuce/issues/92/events", "updated_at": "2011-04-15T22:12:42Z", "labels_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/gabrielfalcao/lettuce/issues/92/labels{/name}", "labels": [], "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/gabrielfalcao/lettuce/issues/92/comments", "html_url": "https://github.com/gabrielfalcao/lettuce/issues/92", "number": 92, "assignee": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/gabrielfalcao/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/gabrielfalcao/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/gabrielfalcao/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/gabrielfalcao", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/gabrielfalcao/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/gabrielfalcao", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/gabrielfalcao/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://gravatar.com/avatar/3fa0df5c54f5ac0f8652d992d7d24039?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F0614053c29836afdd915d777401128a9.png&r=x", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/gabrielfalcao/repos", "receiv