{"body": "Lettuce test runner should provide a syntax that allows to pass command-line options that are later-on evaluated by the test logic (before hooks) or \"terrain.py\" to setup specific configuration information.\r\n\r\nEXAMPLE:\r\nA testsuite should be a applied to an embedded system.\r\nIn general, you have several such testbeds that are distinguished by name or hostname.\r\nIt should be apply the testsuite either on \"testbed1\" or \"testbed2\".\r\n\r\n  shell> lettuce --test-param=\"testbed=testbed1\"\r\n\r\nLater-on in the test logic:\r\n\r\n  testbed = lettuce.test_params.get(\"testbed\", \"testbed1\")\r\n  # -- Setup remaining configuration to use this testbed.\r\n\r\nNOTE:\r\nPython >= 2.6 provides a \"json\" module \r\n(ALTERNATIVE: simplejson if not available => Python < 2.6).\r\nThis could be used to load more complex test data as test params.\r\n", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/gabrielfalcao/lettuce/issues/68/events", "updated_at": "2013-08-14T03:37:04Z", "labels_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/gabrielfalcao/lettuce/issues/68/labels{/name}", "labels": [{"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/gabrielfalcao/lettuce/labels/brainstorm", "color": "454545", "name": "brainstorm"}], "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/gabrielfalcao/lettuce/issues/68/comments", "html_url": "https://github.com/gabrielfalcao/lettuce/issues/68", "number": 68, "assignee": null, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jenisys/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jenisys/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jenisys/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/jenisys", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jenisys/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/jenisys", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jenisys/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://gravatar.com/avatar/3c3e5d70005d0fa4e748b71d0518b07d?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F7719e85bf6