{"body": "If I start with a feature with regex magic characters in it:\r\n\r\n```gherkin\r\nFeature:\r\n    Scenario:\r\n        Given I have an (undefined) step\r\n```\r\n\r\nIt will suggest code like this:\r\n\r\n```python\r\n@step(u'Given I have an (undefined) step')\r\ndef given_i_have_an_undefined_step(step):\r\n    assert False, 'This step must be implemented'\r\n```\r\n\r\nHowever, this won't match the step because the magic characters haven't been escaped, so if you put in that code it will still be undefined (or succeed when it shouldn't if you had, for example, `.` or `*` in the match).\r\n\r\n`re.escape` should be brought to bear on the matter.", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/gabrielfalcao/lettuce/issues/246/events", "updated_at": "2012-04-10T14:46:06Z", "labels_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/gabrielfalcao/lettuce/issues/246/labels{/name}", "labels": [{"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/gabrielfalcao/lettuce/labels/0.2+-+kryptonite", "color": "42c255", "name": "0.2 - kryptonite"}, {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/gabrielfalcao/lettuce/labels/low-priority", "color": "d7e102", "name": "low-priority"}], "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/gabrielfalcao/lettuce/issues/246/comments", "html_url": "https://github.com/gabrielfalcao/lettuce/issues/246", "number": 246, "assignee": null, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/chris-morgan/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/chris-morgan/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/chris-morgan/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/chris-morgan", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/chris-morgan/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/chris-morgan", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/chris-morgan/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://gravatar.com/avatar/16a138ff3b9c8f1663f8a0613c47b60a?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F9f463cda317c616a88c77c3ebfd398a2.png&r=x", "r