{"body": "We noticed that \"Given/Then/When/And\" is included in the string that is passed to the step regexes. We think that is the reason why most lettuce steps are written without ^ and $ to delimit the matching regexes, this makes it hard for developers to write strict regexes.\r\n\r\nFor us this has lead to the problem that a step definition with a short regex caught the step that was intended for a step with a longer regex (e.g. lettuce_webdriver's \"should see\" vs \"should see in seconds\").\r\n\r\nThis took us quite some time to debug. :-)\r\n\r\nIn Cucumber only the part after the given/when/then/and prefix is handed to the steps for matching, with the reasoning, that the prefix is only for the writer of the steps to make it easier for him to show his intent, but not for the step definitions, which should work with any of the prefixes. I.e. in Cucumber you could even replace Given/When/Then/And by asterisks and it would still work just the same.", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/gabrielfalcao/lettuce/issues/170/events", "updated_at": "2014-01-21T09:26:30Z", "labels_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/gabrielfalcao/lettuce/issues/170/labels{/name}", "labels": [{"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/gabrielfalcao/lettuce/labels/low-priority", "color": "d7e102", "name": "low-priority"}], "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/gabrielfalcao/lettuce/issues/170/comments", "html_url": "https://github.com/gabrielfalcao/lettuce/issues/170", "number": 170, "assignee": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/gabrielfalcao/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/gabrielfalcao/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/gabrielfalcao/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/gabrielfalcao", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/gabrielfalcao/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/gabrielfalcao", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/gabrielfalcao/subscription