{"body": "lettuce.world is a thread.local variable, used to store some temporary global data. But it is global, thus stuff stays there for the whole test run.\n\n```\nScenario: Adding stuff to my list\n  Given I am the registered customer\n  And my list of stuff is empty\n  When I add some stuff\n  Then check that stuff is indeed there\n```\n\nThe step \"I am the (registered|anonymous) customer\" may create/fetch some test customer and set it local to current scenario. The next step \"my list of stuff is empty\" clears the list of current (from the local context) customer. Other steps run also in the context of current scenario, using the customer set by the first step.\n\nIt will be a good feature to implement step.scenario.context and step.feature.context dicts that hold the context local to scenario and feature. These dicts will be automatically cleared after scenario/feature has been run. These local contexts will keep global world stuff clean.", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/gabrielfalcao/lettuce/issues/283/events", "updated_at": "2012-08-24T14:28:14Z", "labels_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/gabrielfalcao/lettuce/issues/283/labels{/name}", "labels": [], "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/gabrielfalcao/lettuce/issues/283/comments", "html_url": "https://github.com/gabrielfalcao/lettuce/issues/283", "number": 283, "assignee": null, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/SardarNL/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/SardarNL/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/SardarNL/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/SardarNL", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/SardarNL/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/SardarNL", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/SardarNL/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://gravatar.com/avatar/301e3b289987b0d01d28ae49a2030e3a?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F19453a014be4b45f475dccacfcbb3ef3