{"body": "Lettuce runs Django's builtin-server in background, but that server doesn't serve up static files. That is an issue if you need the javascript and css files. I used the following modifications to lettuce/django/server.py:\r\n\r\nChange:\r\n````from django.core.servers.basehttp import AdminMediaHandler\r\n````\r\n\r\nTo:\r\n````from django.core.servers.basehttp import AdminMediaHandler\r\nfrom django.contrib.staticfiles.handlers import StaticFilesHandler\r\n````\r\n\r\nand:\r\n````httpd.set_app(handler)\r\n````\r\nto:\r\n````handler = StaticFilesHandler(handler)\r\nhttpd.set_app(handler)\r\n````\r\n\r\nNot sure if this is the right approach, so throwing it out here. \r\n", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/gabrielfalcao/lettuce/issues/150/events", "updated_at": "2012-01-10T12:24:41Z", "labels_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/gabrielfalcao/lettuce/issues/150/labels{/name}", "labels": [{"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/gabrielfalcao/lettuce/labels/bug", "color": "ff0000", "name": "bug"}, {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/gabrielfalcao/lettuce/labels/in+analysis", "color": "002bff", "name": "in analysis"}], "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/gabrielfalcao/lettuce/issues/150/comments", "html_url": "https://github.com/gabrielfalcao/lettuce/issues/150", "number": 150, "assignee": null, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/adriaant/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/adriaant/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/adriaant/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/adriaant", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/adriaant/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/adriaant", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/adriaant/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://gravatar.com/avatar/ca24f42ddca2e7c632cf95f1e755ab89?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2Fd65193adc573eb8fdcb0c0d09db7208c.png&r=x", "repos_url": "https://api.github.