{"body": "When dealing with more than one examples block in an outlined scenario, all outlines are executed.\r\n\r\nA simple example:\r\n\r\n    Scenario Outline: Add two numbers\r\n        Given I have entered <input_1> into the calculator\r\n        And I have entered <input_2> into the calculator\r\n        When I press <button>\r\n        Then the result should be <output> on the screen\r\n      \r\n        Examples:\r\n          | input_1 | input_2 | button | output |\r\n          | 20      | 30      | add    | 50     |\r\n          | 2       | 5       | add    | 7      |\r\n          | 0       | 40      | add    | 40     |\r\n  \r\n        Examples:\r\n          | input_1 | input_2 | button | output |\r\n          | 20      | 33      | add    | 53     |\r\n          | 12      | 40      | add    | 52     |\r\n\r\nWill generate this outlines list:\r\n\r\n    [\r\n        {'input_1': '20', 'input_2': '30', 'button': 'add', 'output': '50'},\r\n        {'input_1': '2', 'input_2': '5', 'button': 'add', 'output': '7'},\r\n        {'input_1': '0', 'input_2': '40', 'button': 'add', 'output': '40'},\r\n        {'input_1': '20', 'input_2': '33', 'button': 'add', 'output': '53'},\r\n        {'input_1': '12', 'input_2': '40', 'button': 'add', 'output': '52'},\r\n    ]\r\n\r\n\r\nLet me know what do you think about it :)\r\n", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/gabrielfalcao/lettuce/issues/79/events", "updated_at": "2010-11-04T20:54:14Z", "labels_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/gabrielfalcao/lettuce/issues/79/labels{/name}", "labels": [], "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/gabrielfalcao/lettuce/issues/79/comments", "html_url": "https://github.com/gabrielfalcao/lettuce/pull/79", "number": 79, "assignee": null, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/fsouza/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/fsouza/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/fsouza/orgs", "url": "https://api.gi