{"body": "\r\n\r\nExample, let's say that we have this step in a feature file:\r\n\r\n\tGiven I have the following photos in the database:\r\n\t  | title             | filename  |\r\n\t  | Brick in the wall | brick.jpg |\r\n\t  | People            | crew.jpg  |\r\n\t\r\nand this HTML:\r\n\r\n\t<ul id=\"photos\">\r\n\t  <li>\r\n\t\t<img src=\"/path/to/brick.jpg\" alt=\"Brick in the wall\" />\r\n\t  </li>\r\n\t  <li>\r\n\t\t<img src=\"/path/to/crew.jpg\" alt=\"People\" />\r\n\t  </li>\r\n\t</ul>\r\n\r\nnowadays it should be implemented with:\r\n\tfrom sure import that\r\n\tfrom lettuce import world, step\r\n\r\n\t@step(ur'I have the following photos in the database:')\r\n\tdef have_these_photos(step):\r\n\t    items = world.browser.cssselect(\"ul#photos > li > img\")\r\n    \r\n\t\tassert that(items).len_is(step.hashes)\r\n\t\t# notice this:\r\n\t\ttitles = [h[\"title\"] for h in step.hashes]\r\n\t\r\n\t\tassert that(items).in_each(\"attrib['alt']\").matches(titles)\r\n\t\r\nbut could be:\r\n\r\n\t@step(ur'I have the following photos in the database:')\r\n\tdef have_these_photos(step):\r\n\t    items = world.browser.cssselect(\"ul#photos > li > img\")\r\n    \r\n\t\tassert that(items).len_is(step.hashes)\r\n\t\tassert that(items).in_each(\"attrib['alt']\").matches(step.hashes.values_under(\"title\"))\r\n\r\nan so on...\r\nas long as the solution avoids the overuse of list comprehensions", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/gabrielfalcao/lettuce/issues/64/events", "updated_at": "2011-04-12T16:41:24Z", "labels_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/gabrielfalcao/lettuce/issues/64/labels{/name}", "labels": [{"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/gabrielfalcao/lettuce/labels/brainstorm", "color": "454545", "name": "brainstorm"}, {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/gabrielfalcao/lettuce/labels/in+analysis", "color": "002bff", "name": "in analysis"}], "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/gabrielfalcao/lettuce/issues/64/comments", "html_url": "https://github.