{"body": "I'm really enjoying lettuce. I'm using it to test a hypermedia API project built with Flask. The integration has been very smooth. However, I'm wondering if there is some way to improve the multiline strings feature that does not require lots of double quotes. Here's an example scenario:\r\n\r\n```gherkin\r\nScenario: Creating a User\r\n  Given an access token with global scope\r\n  When I make a POST request to \"/users\" with the body:\r\n  \"\"\"\r\n  \"  {                                \"\r\n  \"    \"email\": \"joe@somewhere.com\",  \"\r\n  \"    \"password\": \"password\"         \"\r\n  \"  }                                \"\r\n  \"\"\"\r\n  Then I should get a 201 status code\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe JSON data is very annoying to manage with all the double quotes required by JSON documents and by lettuce to support the multiline string. It would be awesome if I could just write is as such:\r\n\r\n```gherkin\r\nScenario: Creating a User\r\n  Given an access token with global scope\r\n  When I make a POST request to \"/users\" with the body:\r\n  \"\"\"\r\n  {\r\n    \"email\": \"joe@somewhere.com\",\r\n    \"password\": \"password\"\r\n  }\r\n  \"\"\"\r\n  Then I should get a 201 status code\r\n```\r\n\r\nCheers!", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/gabrielfalcao/lettuce/issues/425/events", "updated_at": "2014-01-24T18:15:31Z", "labels_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/gabrielfalcao/lettuce/issues/425/labels{/name}", "labels": [], "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/gabrielfalcao/lettuce/issues/425/comments", "html_url": "https://github.com/gabrielfalcao/lettuce/issues/425", "number": 425, "assignee": null, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mattupstate/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mattupstate/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mattupstate/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/mattupstate", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/