{"body": "This happens when the number of steps is greater than 256. Even if all steps have passed, overall failure is reported. It is due to line 1258 in core.py:\r\n```\r\n@property\r\n    def passed(self):\r\n        return self.total_steps is len(self.steps_passed)\r\n```\r\nThis will not work due to reasons mentioned here: http://stackoverflow.com/questions/306313/python-is-operator-behaves-unexpectedly-with-integers\r\n\r\nThe fix is simple:\r\n```\r\n@property\r\n    def passed(self):\r\n        return self.total_steps == len(self.steps_passed)\r\n```\r\nThank you so much for including this fix in your codebase.", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/gabrielfalcao/lettuce/issues/364/events", "updated_at": "2014-02-04T10:26:09Z", "labels_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/gabrielfalcao/lettuce/issues/364/labels{/name}", "labels": [], "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/gabrielfalcao/lettuce/issues/364/comments", "html_url": "https://github.com/gabrielfalcao/lettuce/issues/364", "number": 364, "assignee": null, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/behappyrightnow/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/behappyrightnow/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/behappyrightnow/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/behappyrightnow", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/behappyrightnow/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/behappyrightnow", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/behappyrightnow/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://gravatar.com/avatar/c2cb97b6db74401e0e3a8c56ea9e9ea3?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F17dce5d77f6c30c49299a81edf843dda.png&r=x", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/behappyrightnow/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/behappyrightnow/received_events", "gravatar_id": "c2cb97b6db74401e0e3a8c56ea9e9ea3", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/behappyrightnow/starred{/o