{"body": "While developing tests under the Selenium webdriver it's difficult to see what's going on and if the tests are failing because they're written badly or because the app is broken.  To get around this I added a delay:\r\n\r\n    DEBUG = True\r\n    ...\r\n    @after.each_scenario\r\n    def slow_down(scenario):\r\n        if DEBUG:\r\n            time.sleep(3)\r\n\r\nAt some point I'll probably need to have this method wait for user input...\r\n\r\nIt'd be nice to have a command-line option to delay by some number of seconds, with some value like '-1' translating to \"hit enter to continue\":\r\n\r\n```$ lettuce --delay=-1```\r\n\r\n```$ django-admin.py harvest --delay=5```", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/gabrielfalcao/lettuce/issues/152/events", "updated_at": "2011-07-07T15:09:53Z", "labels_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/gabrielfalcao/lettuce/issues/152/labels{/name}", "labels": [], "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/gabrielfalcao/lettuce/issues/152/comments", "html_url": "https://github.com/gabrielfalcao/lettuce/issues/152", "number": 152, "assignee": null, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/krid/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/krid/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/krid/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/krid", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/krid/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/krid", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/krid/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://gravatar.com/avatar/bff39e07681b606b455a04ac5e850b24?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F915b288c81604a55624ed6c1f308813c.png&r=x", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/krid/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/krid/received_events", "gravatar_id": "bff39e07681b606b455a04ac5e850b24", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/krid/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "site_admin": false, "login": "