{"body": "- you can write \"Background:\" section in feature files. It must be after the description of feature.\r\n- you can use \"--tags\" parameter to specify tags\r\n- you can use \"--disable-overlap\" parameter to disable overlapping in colored shell output. Use it with colored output in places, where not all ANSI escape sequences supported (e.g. Console output in Jenkins ver. 1.409.2)\r\n- you can use \"--with-html\" to enable html report\r\n- you can use \"--html-file\" to specify html report file if parameter \"--with-html\" used\r\n- now on graph in Jenkins you can see count of scenarios, not steps. But if scenario failed - you can find information about steps and their statuses with stacktrace on error.\r\n\r\nFor html report pull request https://github.com/gabrielfalcao/lettuce/pull/85 was used.\r\n\r\n**Feature example:**\r\n\r\n        @ftag1 @ftag2\r\n        Feature: Manage databases\r\n            feature's description\r\n        \r\n        Background:\r\n            Given connection to host\r\n            And blablabla\r\n\r\n        @tag1 @tag2\r\n        Scenario: List databases\r\n            When I get list of databases\r\n            Then I should see list of databases\r\n\r\n**Execute scenarios with tag \"@tag1\" or \"@tag2\":**\r\n\r\n        lettuce -t tag1,tag2\r\n\r\n**Execute scenarios with tag \"@tag1\" but not \"@tag2\":**\r\n\r\n        lettuce -t tag1,~tag2", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/gabrielfalcao/lettuce/issues/195/events", "updated_at": "2012-02-21T09:53:21Z", "labels_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/gabrielfalcao/lettuce/issues/195/labels{/name}", "labels": [], "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/gabrielfalcao/lettuce/issues/195/comments", "html_url": "https://github.com/gabrielfalcao/lettuce/pull/195", "number": 195, "assignee": null, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/vitali-ausianik/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/vitali-ausianik/events{/p