{"body": "Hey, Gabriel!\r\n\r\nHow are you doing ?\r\nIn some cases, I need to pass optional values to the hash that a I use to populate my objects, like this:\r\n\r\n| title             | subtitle       |  header            |\r\n| title1           | subtitle1      |                        |\r\n| title2           | subtitle2      |  some header   |\r\n\r\nSo, in strings.py, you get the values directly using data[key] and, in my case, I receive a KeyError.\r\nThis commit changes the way you get this value, using data.get(key, \"\"). So now I can pass (or not) some value.\r\n\r\nIf there is another way to solve my problem, please tell me. If not, please consider my patch :)\r\n\r\nThanks a lot.\r\n\r\nHugs,\r\nBarbosa", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/gabrielfalcao/lettuce/issues/136/events", "updated_at": "2011-05-08T19:56:39Z", "labels_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/gabrielfalcao/lettuce/issues/136/labels{/name}", "labels": [], "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/gabrielfalcao/lettuce/issues/136/comments", "html_url": "https://github.com/gabrielfalcao/lettuce/pull/136", "number": 136, "assignee": null, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/barbosa/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/barbosa/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/barbosa/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/barbosa", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/barbosa/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/barbosa", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/barbosa/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://gravatar.com/avatar/700c1db9f2cce6b3cd626c0eb9fc9b34?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2Fff10e36b40282036b3a92f2c9fdb614c.png&r=x", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/barbosa/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/barbosa/received_events", "gravatar_id": "700c1db9f2cce6b3cd626c0eb9fc9b34", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/b